.TH "svc_rdma_build_read_segment" 9 "svc_rdma_build_read_segment" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
svc_rdma_build_read_segment \- Build RDMA Read WQEs to pull one RDMA segment
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" svc_rdma_build_read_segment
.BI "(struct svc_rdma_read_info *info "  ","
.BI "const struct svc_rdma_segment *segment "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "info" 12
context for ongoing I/O
.IP "segment" 12
co-ordinates of remote memory to be read
.SH "RETURN"
0: the Read WR chain was constructed successfully
-EINVAL: there were not enough rq_pages to finish
-ENOMEM: allocating a local resources failed
-EIO: a DMA mapping error occurred
